# POSITIVE CONTROL for the #128 guard (and first direct harness coverage of the fetch
# hook): a real system's 0-byte cloud stub still triggers --download and gets filled —
# proving the (LODORGM) guard did not over-match and the invoke harness actually runs
# the hook. After the fill, the save check runs (sticky engine line has no TSV rows ->
# no restore prompt -> silent launch).
desc fetch hook: a real 0-byte stub still downloads (guard does not over-match)
invoke prehook
config paired
romarg Roms/Game Boy Advance (GBA)/✘ Zelda.gba
sdfile Roms/Game Boy Advance (GBA)/✘ Zelda.gba
engine 0|RESULT downloaded=1
expect_exit 0
expect_trace ENGINE --download
expect_file_has Roms/Game Boy Advance (GBA)/✘ Zelda.gba	DLBYTES
